result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Cianna L Jones appeared by video.  Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Brad Alan Vorpahl in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defense counsel in trial in another court. Court reviewed progress of agreement. Case adjourned for review hearing, Branch 17.
Review hearing scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Cianna L Jones in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire previously received and efiled.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the case transferred to Judge Stark, Branch 17 for a review hearing.  Review hearing scheduled for October 25, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Addendum to plea questionnaire/waiver of rights, Received and Filed.
Deferred Prosecution Agreement, Received and Filed.

Defendant Cianna L Jones in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cianna L Jones appeared by video means with Attorney.  Case is on a DPA track.    DPA Hearing scheduled in Branch 37.   All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 09:00 am.

  Indigency hearing scheduled for May 26, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Cianna L Jones in court.  Jennifer Jean Tate appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
